Package: rembg
Type: Package
Title: Remove Image Backgrounds with Pre-Trained Segmentation Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Troy", "Hernandez", email = "troy.hernandez@pm.me",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-4248-604X")),
    person("cornball.ai", role = "cph"))
Description: Remove the background from an image using pre-trained deep
    learning segmentation models (U-2-Net, ISNet, BiRefNet and others) run
    through the 'ONNX' Runtime via the 'onnxr' package. Given an image, a
    model predicts a foreground alpha matte which is composited to produce a
    cutout with a transparent (or solid-colour) background. Models are
    downloaded on first use and cached locally, sharing the cache with the
    Python 'rembg' package (<https://github.com/danielgatis/rembg>), of which
    this is an R port.
